The 2018 African Banker Awards nominees have been announced, with a number of African banks shortlisted and featuring in several categories, showing another strong year for the continent.
The nominees for the awards are dominated by Nigeria, Kenya, Morocco and Mauritius.
The awards, which are hosted by African Banker magazine, will be held during the Annual Meetings of the African Development Bank (AfDB) at the end of May in Busan, South Korea.
The finalists, selected by an expert judging panel of bankers and business leaders, will be announced at the ceremony which will take place on Wednesday, May 22.
– African News Agency (ANA)


